# Overview, Configuration & Interface

## Module Overview

The Product Attribute Management module of Solusquare Commerce Cloud allows defining and organizing the characteristics of products sold on the platform. It offers the ability to create attribute typologies, i.e., groups of attributes, and associate them with different product types. This organization facilitates consistent and multilingual management of product information, essential for clear presentation adapted to targeted markets.

This module is particularly useful for enriching product sheets with specific data such as color, size, or any other relevant criteria. It also allows managing attribute options, notably colors with their specific codes, and using these attributes as filters in product searches. Thus, it helps improve the user experience and the relevance of results in the catalog.

## General Workflow

1. Access the "Attributes" section in the Products menu of the back office.  
2. Search for existing attributes using filters (country, product type, attribute).  
3. Create a new attribute by entering its multilingual labels and associating it with one or more product types.  
4. Modify an existing attribute to update its labels, external code, or properties (filter, color).  
5. Manage an attributeâ€™s options by adding or modifying possible values with their multilingual labels and color codes.  
6. Organize color options into groups for better classification.  
7. Prioritize the display order of attributes for each product type.  
8. Delete an attribute or an association if necessary, with confirmation.  
9. Validate changes so they are applied to the product catalog.

## Attribute Management

### Create an Attribute

To create a new attribute, enter its labels in all active languages and associate it with one or more product types.

Steps:  

1. Go to Products > Attributes > Add.  
2. Select one or more associated product types (hold CTRL for multi-selection).  
3. In the table, for each row, enter a label for the new attribute in each displayed language.  
4. Do not select an existing attribute on the same row if a new attribute is entered.  
5. Click "Validate" to save.

### Modify an Attribute

To modify an existing attribute, update its labels, external code, or properties.

Steps:  

1. Search for the attribute using the search form.  
2. Click the edit icon corresponding to the attribute.  
3. Update the labels in the different languages.  
4. Modify the "Filter" and "Is a color" options if necessary.  
5. Save the changes.

### Duplicate an Attribute

Direct duplication is not offered in the interface. To create a similar attribute, use the add function by entering the same labels and associations.

### Prioritize Attributes

The display order of attributes is defined by a sort field associated with each product type.

Steps:  

1. When creating or modifying, set the position (sort) of each attribute.  
2. The order is taken into account in the display of product sheets and filters.  
3. Validate changes to apply the new order.

## Fields Table

| Name            | Type    | Required | Description                                              |
| --------------- | ------- | -------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| attribut_id     | numeric | Yes      | Unique identifier of the attribute                       |
| pays_id         | text    | Yes      | Country where the attribute applies                      |
| langue_id       | text    | Yes      | Language of the label                                    |
| libelle         | text    | Yes      | Label of the attribute in the corresponding language     |
| code_ext        | text    | No       | External code of the attribute                           |
| filtre          | integer | No       | Indicates if the attribute is used as a filter (1 = yes) |
| est_une_couleur | boolean | No       | Indicates if the attribute represents a color (1 = yes)  |

## Configuration Best Practices

For optimal attribute management, always enter labels in all active languages to ensure multilingual consistency. Associate attributes only with relevant product types to avoid unnecessary overload. Use the "Filter" and "Is a color" options judiciously to improve navigation and search in the catalog. Finally, prioritize the display order of attributes to guarantee a clear and intuitive presentation on product sheets.
